CatDescriptText: Walter Moore, car washer, 2329 Fifth Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you believe Negroes, who get public assistance, do more cheating than whites?" answer reads: "I wouldn't know. I know nothing about it, I know that cheating is going on, but I can't say who does the greater amount of cheating."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Walter Moore wearing hat, moustache, striped shirt, and dark leather jacket, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade with sign that reads "S...EY Co. H... And H[abada]shers," Liberty Avenue, Downtown
